    <h1>Clonidine Toxicity</h1>
    
    <div class="alert">
        <strong>"One Pill Can Kill" Warning:</strong> Clonidine is a central alpha-2 agonist. A single 0.1 mg pill can cause severe toxicity in a toddler. It closely mimics opioid overdose.
    </div>

    <h2>Clinical Presentation</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Vitals:</strong> Bradycardia, hypotension, respiratory depression, hypothermia.</li>
        <li><strong>Neuro:</strong> Profound lethargy, coma, miosis (pinpoint pupils).</li>
        <li><strong>Note:</strong> May present with paradoxical transient hypertension initially due to peripheral alpha-1 stimulation before central alpha-2 effects dominate.</li>
    </ul>
    <hr>
    <h2>Weight-Based Resuscitation & Antidotes</h2>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>1. Naloxone (Narcan)</h3>
        <p>May reverse altered mental status and respiratory depression, though results are inconsistent. High doses are often required.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Pediatric Dose:</strong> 0.1 mg/kg IV/IM/IN. Max single dose: 2 mg.</li>
            <li><strong>Adult Dose:</strong> 0.4 - 2 mg IV/IM/IN. May escalate up to 10 mg.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>2. Atropine</h3>
        <p>For hemodynamically significant bradycardia.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Pediatric Dose:</strong> 0.02 mg/kg IV. Minimum dose 0.1 mg (to avoid paradoxical bradycardia). Max single dose: 0.5 mg.</li>
            <li><strong>Adult Dose:</strong> 0.5 - 1 mg IV every 3-5 minutes. Max total dose: 3 mg.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>3. IV Fluids & Vasopressors</h3>
        <p>For hypotension unresponsive to fluid resuscitation.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Fluid Bolus:</strong> 20 mL/kg Isotonic Crystalloid.</li>
            <li><strong>Norepinephrine or Epinephrine:</strong> Start at 0.05 - 0.1 mcg/kg/min IV. Titrate to effect.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
